Prostate cancer screening: to pass an examination or not?
The PSA test yielded erroneous results that were wrongly negative or even wrongly positive, which led to unnecessary medical procedures.
All this further increased the hesitancy of men, who already so reluctant to go to the examination at all.
To be examined or not?
We asked for the opinion of two experts.
In studies conducted in the USA, a high degree of contamination between individual tested groups has manifested itself, so it is difficult to interpret these results and make valuable recommendations.
Another study, this time European, found a difference in mortality between patients who underwent the examination and those who did not.
This study also showed after a 12-year interval that those who did not go to the examination had a 30 to 40% higher risk of metastases.
Therefore, I recommend an examination from the age of 50 or from the age of 40 if your direct relative had prostate cancer.
Men of African American ancestry are also more at risk.
The key is to make the right decision as soon as the cancer is discovered.
There are aggressive types of cancer and such types that are incurable.
It is therefore necessary to correctly explain to the patient the degree of danger of his type of cancer, to offer him possible alternatives, not necessarily to treat prostate cancer that does not have an impact on life in the long term, and to focus in these cases rather on active surveillance of the disease.
Today, many men who have been diagnosed with cancer are not treated because their type of cancer is not aggressive and does not threaten them with life.
Rather, we will suggest active surveillance and, in the event of disease progression, we will offer treatment.
More and more often and with greater precision, we set criteria that help in deciding which type of treatment to treat and which not.
Therefore, I recommend that you do an examination.
However, it is important to have an interview with a doctor and determine whether it is appropriate to undergo an examination or not.
